div1.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF BEN WA, FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS FOR TUNG KEE.

This cause having come on for hearing this day, upon the verified petition of Ben Wa for a writ of habeas corpus for Tung Kee, and the court having read the said petition and being fully advised in the permises,

IT IS NOW ORDERED that Ellis De Bruler, as commissioner of immigration of the United States, who has possession of the said Tung Kee, show cause to this court upon the day of July, 1912, at the hour of ten o'clock A.M., on that day, why a writ of habeas corpus should not be issued directing him to release the said Tung Kee.
Done in open court this day of July, 1912.
Enter This order refused July 9th 1912 C.H. Hanford
